(1) Any person other than the Corporation who— (a) operates or offers to operate a postal service ; or (b) collects, conveys, delivers or deals with any letter otherwise than as permitted by or under this section; shall be guilty of an offence and shall be liable on conviction to a fine not exceeding two thousand five hundred penalty units or to imprisonment for a term not exceeding three months, or to both, for every letter in respect of which the offence is committed.
